        B12 | THE STRAITS TIMES THURSDAY, DECEMBER 3, 2020 | | | OBITUARIES FOR BOOKINGS AND ENQUIRIES 1800-289-9988 6319-5192 or “Be strong and steadfast! Do not fear nor be dismayed, for the Lord, your God, is with you wherever you go.” Joshua 1:9 STEPHEN LEONG CHONG TUCK Led a fruitful life for 72 years. Returned home to be with the Lord on 1 December 2020. Dearly missed and cherished by all loved ones. Wife: Sharon Kwok Yim Lui Daughters: Leong JiaHui Sherynn Ann (deceased) & Leong JiaXin Sheryl Mary Siblings & Spouses: Leong Sook Yee & Tan Swee Beng
Leong Shook Ken & Lee Liat Cheng (deceased) Leong Chong Kwong Peter & Tan Mui Huang Sally Leong Sook Fun Sharon & Chun Wai Kok Nephews/ Nieces & Spouses: Brian Lee Ying Wah & Lie Ming Or Belinda Lee May Ee & Andrew Chan Pak Sing Elaine Tan Hsu-Yen & Yong Wei Sean Terence Tan Tien Ming & Winnie Guo 49th Anniversar­y In Loving Memory Of And all relatives & friends.
Wake is held at Church of St. Stephen, 30 Sallim Road, Singapore 387639 on 3 & 4 Dec 2020 (Thur & Fri) from 10am to 10pm.
Night service will be held on 4 Dec 2020 (Fri) at 8pm. (RET) MAJOR STEPHEN KOONG YUE HONG Age: 85 was called home to be with the Lord on 24 November 2020. Funeral Mass will be held on 5 Dec 2020 (Sat) at 3.30pm, thereafter cortege leaves at 4.15pm for
Mandai Crematoriu­m Hall 2 for cremation at 5.15pm. We, the family of the late Stephen Koong, wish to express our heartfelt appreciati­on to relatives, friends and members of Bethesda Hall (AMK) for their kind assistance, attendance, condolence­s, donations and wreaths during our recent bereavemen­t. Special Thanks to Doctors and Nurses of Sengkang Hospital HDU Ward 33 Room 17; Dr. Tay Kay Yaw, Associate Prof. Chai Josiah and
Adjunct Assistant Prof. Yu Chun Sing of Tan Tock Seng Hospital. GOVINDASAM­Y HACHUTHEN Departed on 3 Dec 1971 Always in our Thoughts Forever in our Hearts Due to COVID19 restrictio­ns on gatherings, kindly contact the family at Tel. 98181340 (Sheryl) prior to wake visiting and attending scheduled services. Deeply missed & always remembered by loved ones. (From L to R) Darren Cheng, CEO • Jenny Tay, MD • Roland Tay, Founder Classified­s obituaries online Find today’s Death announceme­nts in The Straits Times are now digitised to make it easier for the deceased’s next-of-kin to share news of the demise of their loved one. Find the online version of the obituaries published today at : or
